sect2.para:
Now you must choose an &expires;. Usually this will be Never Expires,
		unless there is a specific reason for having your &key;
		expire.

Finally, you must enter a passphrase for the &key; and confirm it.
		This should be a passphrase instead of a password.
		When finished, click OK to generate the new &key;

listitem.para:
To import &keys;
					from a file, select Import from File,
					choose a file, then click OK.

To import &keys;
					from text, select Import from Text,
					paste the text into the text area, then click OK.

No Reason for
					revoking
					the &key; or &subkey;
